Case 21-58, Document 65, 04/13/2021, 3076657, Page1 of 1

UNITED STATES COURT OF APPEALS
FOR THE
SECOND CIRCUIT

At a Stated Term of the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit, held at
the Thurgood Marshall United States Courthouse, 40 Foley Square, in the City of New York, on
the 13th day of April, two thousand twenty one,

United States of America,
Appellee,

ORDER
Docket Nos. 21-58 (L)
21-770 (Con)

v.

Ghislain Maxwell, AKA Sealed Defendant 1,
Defendant - Appellant.

Appellee moves for leave to file a supporting exhibit under seal in opposition to the
appellant's motion for bail.

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED that the motion is GRANTED.

For The Court:
Catherine O'Hagan Wolfe,
Clerk of Court

Catherine O'Hagan Wolfe
UNITED STATES COURT OF APPEALS
SECOND CIRCUIT

DOJ-OGR-00020283
